[Saint-Simon (disambiguation)|Saint-Simon]]\n* [[Simone (disambiguation)|Simone]]\n* [[Simons]]\n*[[Symon]]\n\n{{surname|Simon}}<!-- It does not help to add disambig or hndis tags where the page only contains people who share a surname -->\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Patronymic surnames]]\n[[Category:English-language surnames]]\n[[Category:German-language surnames]]\n[[Category:French-language surnames]]\n[[Category:Jewish surnames]]\n", "text_old": "'''Simon''' is a [[patronymic]] surname deriving from [[Simon (given name)]]. It is also a [[surname]] of [[Old Norse]] origins and a variant of [[Sigmund]], a [[Germanic languages|Germanic]] [[given name]] with roots in proto-Germanic [[wikt:Reconstruction:Proto-Germanic/segaz|''*segaz'']] and [[wikt:Reconstruction:Proto-Germanic/mund\u014d|''*mund\u014d'']], giving a rough translation of \"protection through victory\". <ref>{{cite book |last= Gauch\u00e9 |first= Isebell |title= The A to Z of Names (Revised and Expanded Edition) : Discover the promise your name holds |publisher= Struik Christian Media |location= Cape Town |year= 2012 |isbn= 1415316260 |id= lemma: Siegmund }}</ref> Notable people with this surname include:\n\n{{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}\n\n==A==\n* [[Abbey Simon]] (1920\u20132019), Jewish-American pianist\n* [[Andr\u00e9 Simon (wine)]] (1877\u20131970), French wine expert \n* [[Andr\u00e9 Simon (racing driver)]] (1920\u20132012), former French racing car driver\n* [[Anne Simon]], American science advisor on the TV series ''The X-Files''\n\n==B==\n* [[Barry Simon]] (born 1946), American mathematical physicist\n* [[Barry Simon (politician)]] (1936\u20132004), Australian politician\n* [[Ben Simon]] (born 1978), American ice hockey player\n* [[Bill Simon (politician)]] (born 1951), American businessman and politician\n* [[Bill Simon (musician)]] (born 1920), American jazz musician\n* [[Bob Simon]] (1941\u20132015), American correspondent on CBS News\n\n==C==\n* [[Calvin Simon]]